This paper discusses differential privacy in the context of machine learning, which is a common topic in the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves adding noise to the training data, which is a common technique in the sub-category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses the gradient and loss function, which are common topics in the sub-categories of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the paper involves building a bridge between the local and central models, which is a topic in the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
